# Reflection - Module 02

## What did I learn?

Today I learned that SDLC is not simply a sequence of development phases, but a structured process that helps software teams build quality products efficiently.

I also learned that QA Engineers contribute throughout the SDLC, from understanding requirements to validating software after deployment.

---

## Challenges

I initially believed that QA mainly worked during the Testing phase.

After learning SDLC, I realized that QA should be involved earlier to prevent defects instead of only finding them.

---

